10,000. It's just a number.

Four years ago, almost to the day, I posted a shot celebrating 300 followers. At that time, it was a huge number for me.

Now in 2018, the algorithms have changed, some famous designers have moved away from the platform, work inquires are few, but I'm still here. And staying committed to this community of talented and caring people is still important to me. I'll continue exploring, interacting, and bettering myself here.

My genuine thanks to everyone who has followed me along the way, especially those who have been there since the beginning. Every like, comment, and rebound means more than you know.

Whether you have 300, 3,000 or 30,000 followers, know that a number doesn't define you.

"Tiny victories are still victories."
-Brad Montague

description:
"Young friend,

Do you think I'm made of money? When I was your age I had to work and keep the entire family. A little hard work never hurt anybody. Money doesn't grow on trees, you know. We were grateful to have an orange for Christmas. You don't know you're born. And stop crying or I'll give you something to cry about.

Come here, it‚Äôll be alright. I'll see you in the morning, love. Don't let the bedbugs bite!

Dad"

As intimidating as it used to sound back then, I bet lots of us would gladly go back in time to live those moments with your dad once again: to listen to his stories and let him teach you all sorts of things once again, to go hunting together and to get an awkward, but such a warm dad‚Äôs hug.

So, if you‚Äôd like to bring back the memories of those good times you spent with your dad when you were a child, you‚Äôd appreciate PAPKA - the most honest artificial intelligence, a blockchain-based product we‚Äôve been working on here at Zajno.

The main idea is surely not to replace human relationships but to remind all of us how great it was to always have Dad‚Äôs strong shoulder to lean on when he was always there for us. Maybe it‚Äôll also remind us to call our dear ones a bit more often and care about them as they used to care about us. Love your parents!

What do you think about the idea and the design? Would love to hear from you!

Don‚Äôt forget to follow Zajno on social media and feel free to drop us a line:
Facebook | UpLabs | Twitter | Instagram | Medium |
title: PAPKA - The Most Honest Artificial Intelligence
